<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,895,2001]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,550,895,920]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Description of female terminalia.</emphasis>
Posterior margin of T5 triangular, reddish, with golden microtrichosity and a row of robust, spine-like setae near posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[747,877,932,957]" captionStart="FIGURES 75–80" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,193,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[168,1416,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 75–80. Peckia (Peckia) gulo (Fabricius), female from Pará, Bragança (MPEG). 75. Abdominal sternites and tergites 5 and 6 in ventral view. 76. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 77. Spermatheca in lateral view. 78. Abdomen in posterior view. 79. Abdomen in dorsal view. 80. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 73, 76–78 = 2 mm; 74–75 = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456145/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs 78–80</figureCitation>
). T6 divided into two halves, brown, covered with golden microtrichosity and with grooves on its surface (visible in dry specimens) and robust setae near posterior margin. Spiracles 6 and 7 located on T6. T8 absent (
<figureCitation box="[731,861,1004,1029]" captionStart="FIGURES 75–80" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,193,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[168,1416,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 75–80. Peckia (Peckia) gulo (Fabricius), female from Pará, Bragança (MPEG). 75. Abdominal sternites and tergites 5 and 6 in ventral view. 76. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 77. Spermatheca in lateral view. 78. Abdomen in posterior view. 79. Abdomen in dorsal view. 80. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 73, 76–78 = 2 mm; 74–75 = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456145/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs 75, 78</figureCitation>
). Epiproct triangular, poorly sclerotized, reduced to a patch of setae on the membrane, near the cercus. Cercus covered with fine setae. Hypoproct triangular, covered with long and fine setae (
<figureCitation box="[448,535,1076,1101]" captionStart="FIGURES 75–80" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,193,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[168,1416,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 75–80. Peckia (Peckia) gulo (Fabricius), female from Pará, Bragança (MPEG). 75. Abdominal sternites and tergites 5 and 6 in ventral view. 76. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 77. Spermatheca in lateral view. 78. Abdomen in posterior view. 79. Abdomen in dorsal view. 80. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 73, 76–78 = 2 mm; 74–75 = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456145/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
). ST6 elongate, with a pair of robust setae near posterior margin. ST7 shieldshaped, without setae. ST8 wider than long, with lateral margin curved inward and a row of setae near posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[250,339,1148,1173]" captionStart="FIGURES 75–80" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,193,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[168,1416,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 75–80. Peckia (Peckia) gulo (Fabricius), female from Pará, Bragança (MPEG). 75. Abdominal sternites and tergites 5 and 6 in ventral view. 76. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 77. Spermatheca in lateral view. 78. Abdomen in posterior view. 79. Abdomen in dorsal view. 80. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 73, 76–78 = 2 mm; 74–75 = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456145/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
). Spermathecae globular, with grooves and a small rounded chamber where they receive the spermathecal duct (
<figureCitation box="[369,454,1183,1208]" captionStart="FIGURES 75–80" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,193,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[168,1416,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 75–80. Peckia (Peckia) gulo (Fabricius), female from Pará, Bragança (MPEG). 75. Abdominal sternites and tergites 5 and 6 in ventral view. 76. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 77. Spermatheca in lateral view. 78. Abdomen in posterior view. 79. Abdomen in dorsal view. 80. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 73, 76–78 = 2 mm; 74–75 = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456145/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
